    <div class="portfolio_head">
     <h1 id="portfolio_headText">
      How Big is the Bay?
     </h1>
     <h1 id="portfolio_subText">
      aka, the Bay Area is Huge!
     </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="portfolio_desc">
     <h3 id="portfolio_descText">
      I arrived in San Francisco knowing little about the Bay Area. These maps were done initially as a purely personal study to help me wrap my head around a fundamental feature of the region, but many locals have told me they were as surprised as I was to find out just how large and extensive the Bay Area is relative to New York, Washington DC, Los Angeles, and London. It seems common to talk about the Bay Area as though it were single place, akin to Manhattan, but these map question this notion and point, at least in terms of its physical area, to a regionally defined notion of the Bay.
      <br />
      <br />
     </h3>
    </div>
